stnPptp.name: stnPptp
stnPptp.contactinfo: Spring Tide Networks, Inc. Customer Service Postal: 3 Clock Tower Place Maynard, MA 01754 Tel: 1 888-786-4357 Email: stncs@springtidenet.com
stnPptp.description: The MIB module that describes managed objects of general use by the Point-to-Point Transport Protocol.

MilliSeconds.name: MilliSeconds
MilliSeconds.description: A period of time measured in units of .001 of seconds when used in conjunction with the DISPLAY-HINT will show seconds and fractions of second with a resolution of .001 of a second.

stnPptpAdminState.name: stnPptpAdminState
stnPptpAdminState.description: This object defines the administrative state of this PPTP tunnel domain. Setting this object to 'disabled' causes all tunnels to be immediately disconnected and no further tunnels to be either initiated or accepted.

stnPptpProtocolVersion.name: stnPptpProtocolVersion
stnPptpProtocolVersion.description: Vector of supported PPTP protocol version and revision numbers. Supported versions are identified via a two octet pairing where the first octet indicates the version and the second octet contains the revision.

stnPptpVendorName.name: stnPptpVendorName
stnPptpVendorName.description: This object identifies the Vendor name of the PPTP protocol stack.

stnPptpFirmwareRev.name: stnPptpFirmwareRev
stnPptpFirmwareRev.description: This object defines the firmware revision for the PPTP protocol stack.

stnPptpDomainConfigEntry.name: stnPptpDomainConfigEntry
stnPptpDomainConfigEntry.description: An PPTP Domain configuration entry. An entry in this table may correspond to a single endpoint or a group of tunnel endpoints.

stnPptpDomainStatsTable.name: stnPptpDomainStatsTable
stnPptpDomainStatsTable.description: The PPTP Domain Status and Statistics table.

stnPptpDomainStatsEntry.name: stnPptpDomainStatsEntry
stnPptpDomainStatsEntry.description: An PPTP Domain Stats entry. An entry in this table may correspond to a single endpoint or a group of tunnel endpoints.

stnPptpDomainStatsIdentifier.name: stnPptpDomainStatsIdentifier
stnPptpDomainStatsIdentifier.description: The identifier, usually in the form of a Domain Name (full or partial), describing a single tunnel endpoint or a domain of tunnel endpoints.

stnPptpDomainStatsTotalTunnels.name: stnPptpDomainStatsTotalTunnels
stnPptpDomainStatsTotalTunnels.description: This object returns the total number of tunnels that have successfully reached the established state for this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsFailedTunnels.name: stnPptpDomainStatsFailedTunnels
stnPptpDomainStatsFailedTunnels.description: This object returns the number of tunnels that failed to reach the established state for this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsActiveTunnels.name: stnPptpDomainStatsActiveTunnels
stnPptpDomainStatsActiveTunnels.description: This object returns the number of tunnels that are currently active for this domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsTotalSessions.name: stnPptpDomainStatsTotalSessions
stnPptpDomainStatsTotalSessions.description: This object returns the total number of sessions that have successfully reached the established state for this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsFailedSessions.name: stnPptpDomainStatsFailedSessions
stnPptpDomainStatsFailedSessions.description: This object returns the number of sessions that failed to reach the established state for this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsActiveSessions.name: stnPptpDomainStatsActiveSessions
stnPptpDomainStatsActiveSessions.description: This object returns the number of sessions that are currently active for this domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsControlRecvOctets.name: stnPptpDomainStatsControlRecvOctets
stnPptpDomainStatsControlRecvOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets received for this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsControlRecvPackets.name: stnPptpDomainStatsControlRecvPackets
stnPptpDomainStatsControlRecvPackets.description: This object returns the number of control packets received for this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsControlSendOctets.name: stnPptpDomainStatsControlSendOctets
stnPptpDomainStatsControlSendOctets.description: This object returns the number of control channel octets that were transmitted to tunnel endpoints for this domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsControlSendPackets.name: stnPptpDomainStatsControlSendPackets
stnPptpDomainStatsControlSendPackets.description: This object returns the number of control packets that were transmitted to tunnel endpoints for this domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadRecvOctets.name: stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadRecvOctets
stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadRecvOctets.description: This object returns the number of payload channel octets that were received for this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadRecvPackets.name: stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadRecvPackets
stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadRecvPackets.description: This object returns the number of payload packets that were received for this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadRecvDiscards.name: stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadRecvDiscards
stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadRecvDiscards.description: This object returns the number of received payload packets that were discarded by this this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadSendOctets.name: stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadSendOctets
stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadSendOctets.description: This object returns the number of payload channel octets that were transmitted to tunnel peers within this tunnel domain.

stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadSendPackets.name: stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadSendPackets
stnPptpDomainStatsPayloadSendPackets.description: This object returns the number of payload packets that were transmitted to tunnel peers within this tunnel domain.

stnPptpTunnelConfigEntry.name: stnPptpTunnelConfigEntry
stnPptpTunnelConfigEntry.description: A PPTP tunnel interface configuration entry.

stnPptpTunnelConfigIfIndex.name: stnPptpTunnelConfigIfIndex
stnPptpTunnelConfigIfIndex.description: This value for this object is equal to the value of ifIndex of the Interfaces MIB for tunnel interfaces of type PPTP.

stnPptpTunnelConfigTransport.name: stnPptpTunnelConfigTransport
stnPptpTunnelConfigTransport.description: This object defines the underlying transport media that is in use for this tunnel entry. Different tunnel transports may define MIB extensions to the PPTP tunnel table to realize the transport layer.

stnPptpTunnelStatsTable.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsTable
stnPptpTunnelStatsTable.description: The PPTP tunnel status and statistics table.

stnPptpTunnelStatsEntry.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsEntry
stnPptpTunnelStatsEntry.description: An PPTP tunnel interface stats entry.

stnPptpTunnelStatsIfIndex.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsIfIndex
stnPptpTunnelStatsIfIndex.description: This value for this object is equal to the value of ifIndex of the Interfaces MIB for tunnel interfaces of type PPTP.

stnPptpTunnelStatsLocalTID.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsLocalTID
stnPptpTunnelStatsLocalTID.description: This object contains the local tunnel Identifier.

stnPptpTunnelStatsState.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsState
stnPptpTunnelStatsState.description: This field contains the current state of the control tunnel.

stnPptpTunnelStatsInitiated.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsInitiated
stnPptpTunnelStatsInitiated.description: This object indicates whether the tunnel was initiated locally or by the remote tunnel peer.

stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteHostName.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteHostName
stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteHostName.description: This object contains the host name as discovered during the tunnel establishment phase

stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteVendorName.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteVendorName
stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteVendorName.description: This object identifies the vendor name of the peer's PPTP implementation.

stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteFirmwareRevision.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteFirmwareRevision
stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteFirmwareRevision.description: This object contains the tunnel peer's firmware revision number.

stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteProtocolVersion.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteProtocolVersion
stnPptpTunnelStatsRemoteProtocolVersion.description: This object describes the protocol version and revision of the tunnel peers implementation. The first octet contains the protocol version. The second octet contains the protocol revision.

stnPptpTunnelStatsBearerCapabilities.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsBearerCapabilities
stnPptpTunnelStatsBearerCapabilities.description: This object describes the Bearer Capabilities of the tunnel peer.

stnPptpTunnelStatsFramingCapabilities.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsFramingCapabilities
stnPptpTunnelStatsFramingCapabilities.description: This object describes the Framing Capabilities of the tunnel peer.

stnPptpTunnelStatsControlRecvPackets.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsControlRecvPackets
stnPptpTunnelStatsControlRecvPackets.description: This object contains the number of control packets received on the tunnel.

stnPptpTunnelStatsControlSendPackets.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsControlSendPackets
stnPptpTunnelStatsControlSendPackets.description: This object contains the number of control packets that were transmitted to the tunnel peer.

stnPptpTunnelStatsTotalSessions.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsTotalSessions
stnPptpTunnelStatsTotalSessions.description: This object contains the total number of sessions that this tunnel has successfully connected through to its tunnel peer since this tunnel was created.

stnPptpTunnelStatsFailedSessions.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsFailedSessions
stnPptpTunnelStatsFailedSessions.description: This object contains the total number of sessions that were initiated but failed to reach the established phase.

stnPptpTunnelStatsActiveSessions.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsActiveSessions
stnPptpTunnelStatsActiveSessions.description: This object contains the total number of sessions in the established state for this tunnel.

stnPptpTunnelStatsLastResultCode.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsLastResultCode
stnPptpTunnelStatsLastResultCode.description: This object contains the last value of the result code as described in the Result Code which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

stnPptpTunnelStatsLastErrorCode.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsLastErrorCode
stnPptpTunnelStatsLastErrorCode.description: This object contains the last value of the error code as described in the Result Code which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

stnPptpTunnelStatsLastErrorMessage.name: stnPptpTunnelStatsLastErrorMessage
stnPptpTunnelStatsLastErrorMessage.description: This object contains the last value of the optional message as described in the Result Code which caused the tunnel to disconnect.

stnPptpSessionStatsTable.name: stnPptpSessionStatsTable
stnPptpSessionStatsTable.description: The PPTP session status and statistics table.

stnPptpSessionStatsEntry.name: stnPptpSessionStatsEntry
stnPptpSessionStatsEntry.description: An PPTP session interface stats entry.

stnPptpSessionStatsTunnelIfIndex.name: stnPptpSessionStatsTunnelIfIndex
stnPptpSessionStatsTunnelIfIndex.description: This object identifies the sessions associated PPTP tunnel ifIndex value.

stnPptpSessionStatsHLIfIndex.name: stnPptpSessionStatsHLIfIndex
stnPptpSessionStatsHLIfIndex.description: This object identifies the ifIndex value of the interface that is either below (Lower) the tunnel (if this tunnel endpoint is a PAC) or above (Higher) the tunnel (if this tunnel endpoint is a PNS). For example this could be a DS0 ifIndex on a PAC or it would be the PPP ifIndex on the PNS.

stnPptpSessionStatsLocalCID.name: stnPptpSessionStatsLocalCID
stnPptpSessionStatsLocalCID.description: This object contains the local call identifier for the session.

stnPptpSessionStatsUserName.name: stnPptpSessionStatsUserName
stnPptpSessionStatsUserName.description: This object identifies the peer session name on this interface. This is typically the login name of the remote user. If the user name is unknown to the local tunnel peer then this object will contain a null string.

stnPptpSessionStatsState.name: stnPptpSessionStatsState
stnPptpSessionStatsState.description: This object contains the current state of the session.

stnPptpSessionStatsCallType.name: stnPptpSessionStatsCallType
stnPptpSessionStatsCallType.description: This object indicates the type of call and the role this tunnel peer is providing for this session. For example, pacIncoming(1) indicates that this tunnel peer is acting as a PAC and generated a Incoming-Call-Request to the tunnel peer (the PNS). Note that tunnel peers can be both PAC and PNS simultaneously.

stnPptpSessionStatsCallSerialNumber.name: stnPptpSessionStatsCallSerialNumber
stnPptpSessionStatsCallSerialNumber.description: This object contains the serial number that has been assigned to this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsTxConnectSpeed.name: stnPptpSessionStatsTxConnectSpeed
stnPptpSessionStatsTxConnectSpeed.description: This object returns the last known transmit baud rate for this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsRxConnectSpeed.name: stnPptpSessionStatsRxConnectSpeed
stnPptpSessionStatsRxConnectSpeed.description: This object returns the last known receive baud rate for this session established.

stnPptpSessionStatsCallBearerType.name: stnPptpSessionStatsCallBearerType
stnPptpSessionStatsCallBearerType.description: This object describes the bearer type of this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsFramingType.name: stnPptpSessionStatsFramingType
stnPptpSessionStatsFramingType.description: This object describes the framing type of this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsPhysChanId.name: stnPptpSessionStatsPhysChanId
stnPptpSessionStatsPhysChanId.description: This object contains the physical channel identifier for the session.

stnPptpSessionStatsDNIS.name: stnPptpSessionStatsDNIS
stnPptpSessionStatsDNIS.description: This object identifies the Dialed Number Information String that the PAC obtained from the network for the session. If no DNIS was provided then a null string will be returned.

stnPptpSessionStatsCLID.name: stnPptpSessionStatsCLID
stnPptpSessionStatsCLID.description: This object identifies the Calling Line ID that the PAC obtained from the network for the session. If no CLID was provided then a null string will be returned.

stnPptpSessionStatsSubAddress.name: stnPptpSessionStatsSubAddress
stnPptpSessionStatsSubAddress.description: This object identifies the Sub Address that the PAC obtained from the network for the session. If no Sub Address was provided then a null string will be returned.

stnPptpSessionStatsPrivateGroupID.name: stnPptpSessionStatsPrivateGroupID
stnPptpSessionStatsPrivateGroupID.description: This object identifies the Private Group Identifier used for this tunneled session. If no Private Group Identifier was provided then a null string will be returned.

stnPptpSessionStatsLocalRWS.name: stnPptpSessionStatsLocalRWS
stnPptpSessionStatsLocalRWS.description: This object returns the local send window size for this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsRemoteInitialRWS.name: stnPptpSessionStatsRemoteInitialRWS
stnPptpSessionStatsRemoteInitialRWS.description: This object returns the initial remote send window size for this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsRemotePPD.name: stnPptpSessionStatsRemotePPD
stnPptpSessionStatsRemotePPD.description: This object contains the Packet Processing Delay for the session.

stnPptpSessionStatsRecvZLB.name: stnPptpSessionStatsRecvZLB
stnPptpSessionStatsRecvZLB.description: This object returns the total number of Zero Length Body acknowlegement payload packets received for this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsOutSequence.name: stnPptpSessionStatsOutSequence
stnPptpSessionStatsOutSequence.description: This object returns the total number of packets received for this session which were received out of sequence.

stnPptpSessionStatsSendZLB.name: stnPptpSessionStatsSendZLB
stnPptpSessionStatsSendZLB.description: This object returns the total number of Zero Length Body acknowledgement packets transmitted on this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsAckTimeouts.name: stnPptpSessionStatsAckTimeouts
stnPptpSessionStatsAckTimeouts.description: This object returns the total number of acknowledgement timeouts seen on payload packets for this session.

stnPptpSesssionStatsCurrentRemoteRWS.name: stnPptpSesssionStatsCurrentRemoteRWS
stnPptpSesssionStatsCurrentRemoteRWS.description: This object contains the current remote receive window size as determined by the local flow control mechanism employed.

stnPptpSessionStatsSendSeq.name: stnPptpSessionStatsSendSeq
stnPptpSessionStatsSendSeq.description: This object contains the next send sequence number for for this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsSendSeqAck.name: stnPptpSessionStatsSendSeqAck
stnPptpSessionStatsSendSeqAck.description: This object contains the send sequence number that the tunnel peer has acknowledged for the payload channel. The flow control state can be determined by subtracting the stnPptpSessionStatsSendSeq from stnPptpSessionStatsSendSeqAck and comparing this value to stnPptpSesssionStatsCurrentRemoteRWS.

stnPptpSessionStatsRecvSeq.name: stnPptpSessionStatsRecvSeq
stnPptpSessionStatsRecvSeq.description: This object contains the next receive sequence number expected to be received on this session.

stnPptpSessionStatsRecvSeqAck.name: stnPptpSessionStatsRecvSeqAck
stnPptpSessionStatsRecvSeqAck.description: This object contains the last receive sequence number that was acknowledged back to the tunnel peer for the session.

stnPptpTunnelMapTable.name: stnPptpTunnelMapTable
stnPptpTunnelMapTable.description: The PPTP Tunnel index mapping table.

stnPptpTunnelMapEntry.name: stnPptpTunnelMapEntry
stnPptpTunnelMapEntry.description: An PPTP tunnel index map entry.

stnPptpTunnelMapLocalTID.name: stnPptpTunnelMapLocalTID
stnPptpTunnelMapLocalTID.description: This object contains the local tunnel Identifier.

stnPptpTunnelMapIfIndex.name: stnPptpTunnelMapIfIndex
stnPptpTunnelMapIfIndex.description: This value for this object is equal to the value of ifIndex of the Interfaces MIB for tunnel interfaces of type PPTP.

stnPptpSessionMapTable.name: stnPptpSessionMapTable
stnPptpSessionMapTable.description: The PPTP Session index mapping table.

stnPptpSessionMapEntry.name: stnPptpSessionMapEntry
stnPptpSessionMapEntry.description: An PPTP Session index map entry.

stnPptpSessionMapHLIfIndex.name: stnPptpSessionMapHLIfIndex
stnPptpSessionMapHLIfIndex.description: This object identifies the ifIndex value of the interface that is either below (Lower) the tunnel (if this tunnel endpoint is a PAC) or above (Higher) the tunnel (if this tunnel endpoint is a PNS). For example this could be a DS0 ifIndex on a PAC or it would be the PPP ifIndex on the PNS.

stnPptpSessionMapTunnelIfIndex.name: stnPptpSessionMapTunnelIfIndex
stnPptpSessionMapTunnelIfIndex.description: This object identifies the sessions associated PPTP tunnel ifIndex value.

stnPptpSessionMapLocalCID.name: stnPptpSessionMapLocalCID
stnPptpSessionMapLocalCID.description: This object contains the local call identifier for the session.

stnPptpDomainMapTable.name: stnPptpDomainMapTable
stnPptpDomainMapTable.description: This table provides a mapping between PPTP Domain identifiers, hostnames, and IP-ATM information

stnPptpDomainMapTableEntry.name: stnPptpDomainMapTableEntry
stnPptpDomainMapTableEntry.description: An entry within the STN PPTP Map Table.

stnPptpDomainMapHostName.name: stnPptpDomainMapHostName
stnPptpDomainMapHostName.description: The hostname that maps to the PPTP Domain Identifier.

stnPptpDomainMapType.name: stnPptpDomainMapType
stnPptpDomainMapType.description: Identifiers whether the PPTP Domain maps to an IP subnet or an ATM circuit.

stnPptpDomainMapTypeInfo.name: stnPptpDomainMapTypeInfo
stnPptpDomainMapTypeInfo.description: Provides either IP or ATM specific display info.

stnPptpCompliance.name: stnPptpCompliance
stnPptpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv2 entities which implement the PPTP MIB.

stnPptpConfigGroup.name: stnPptpConfigGroup
stnPptpConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing configuration information of the PPTP protocol, tunnels and sessions.

stnPptpStatsGroup.name: stnPptpStatsGroup
stnPptpStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing status and statistics of the PPTP protocol, tunnels and sessions.

stnPptpDomainGroup.name: stnPptpDomainGroup
stnPptpDomainGroup.description: A collection of objects providing configuration, status and statistics of PPTP tunnel domains.

stnPptpMappingGroup.name: stnPptpMappingGroup
stnPptpMappingGroup.description: A collection of objects providing index mapping.
